{
  "topicId": "m6-t2",
  "title": "Asking About Places and Services",
  "dialect": "darija",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'Where is...?'"
        },
        "text": "To ask where something is in Egyptian Arabic, you use the word 'فين' (feen). It's a versatile question word.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "فين البنك؟",
            "english": "Where is the bank?",
            "transliteration": "Feen el-bank?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "فين أقرب مستشفى؟",
            "english": "Where is the nearest hospital?",
            "transliteration": "Feen aqrab mostashfa?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing 'I want / I need'"
        },
        "text": "To express 'I want' or 'I need', Egyptians use 'أنا عايز' for males and 'أنا عايزة' for females. The pronunciation subtly changes at the end.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا عايز قهوة.",
            "english": "I want coffee. (male speaker)",
            "transliteration": "Ana ʿaayez 'ahwa."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا عايزة أروح المستشفى.",
            "english": "I want to go to the hospital. (female speaker)",
            "transliteration": "Ana ʿayza arooḥ el-mostashfa."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "'Here' and 'There'"
        },
        "text": "When someone gives you directions, they might use 'هنا' for 'here' and 'هناك' for 'there'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "المطعم هنا.",
            "english": "The restaurant is here.",
            "transliteration": "El-maṭʿam hena."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "السوبر ماركت هناك.",
            "english": "The supermarket is there.",
            "transliteration": "Es-supermarket henāk."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "أنا عايز فين؟",
        "english": "Where do I want?",
        "transliteration": "Ana ʿaayez feen?"
      },
      "context": "A slightly confused way to ask where you want to go. More naturally: 'أنا عايز أروح فين؟' (Ana ʿaayez arooḥ feen? - Where do I want to go?)"
    },
    {
